article.headline: Southern Illinois 73, Wichita State 68
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. (AP) -- Randal Falker scored 20 points and Matt Shaw added 18 as Southern Illinois beat Wichita State 73-68 Monday night. Falker shot 8-for-9 from the free-throw line while Shaw grabbed a game-high nine rebounds for the Salukis (11-2, 2-0 Missouri Valley), whose 38-23 halftime lead allowed them to hold on despite being outscored 45-35 in the second half. Wichita State (9-4, 0-2) was led by 20 points from P.J. Couisnard, who finished 7-for-11 from the field. Kyle Wilson added 16 points and Sean Ogirri had 10 for the Shockers, who shot 70 percent (16-for-23) in the second half after a 35 percent (8-for-23) performance before the break. Bryan Mullins scored 13 for Southern Illinois and Tony Young added 10 before fouling out with 1:15 to go in the game. The Salukis finished at 46 percent (24-for-52) shooting, while the Shockers shot 52 percent (24-for-46) overall.
